# Web platform forks

## Pattern

| File | Renders |
|------|---------|
| `index.tsx` | React Native via Gluestack creator |
| `index.web.tsx` | HTML elements for Next.js |

`packages/ui/package.json` exports must point to `.web.tsx` for web-safe components.

## RN → DOM mapping

| React Native | Web |
|--------------|-----|
| `onPress` | `onClick` |
| `secureTextEntry` | `type="password"` |
| `keyboardType="email-address"` | `type="email"` |
| `numberOfLines` | `rows` on `<textarea>` |
| `multiline` | omit (textarea is multiline by default) |

**Never spread unknown props onto DOM nodes.** Destructure RN-only props first.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
function TextareaInput({ multiline: _m, numberOfLines, rows, ...props }, ref) {
  return <textarea rows={rows ?? numberOfLines ?? 4} {...props} ref={ref} />;
}
```

## When adding Gluestack components

1. `pnpm ui:add <name>`
2. If used on web, add/verify `index.web.tsx`
3. Update `@repo/ui` export to `.web.tsx`
4. Test in browser - watch console for invalid DOM attribute warnings

## Icons on web

Use `packages/ui/src/components/ui/icon/index.web.tsx` for SVG icons with `stroke="currentColor"`.
